    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;Segment Routing (SR) allows a flexible definition of end-to-end paths within IGP topologies by encoding paths as sequences of topological subpaths called "segments". These segments are advertised by the link-state routing protocols (IS-IS and OSPF).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This document describes the OSPFv3 extensions required for Segment Routing with the MPLS data plane.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
